result.name: government-procurement-card-hdc
result.notes:
This dataset, published on a quarterly basis, contains details of all expenditure made on the council's Government Procurement Card.

The use of the GPC refers to cards issued under a procurement framework owned by the Crown Commercial Service. The GPCs are used by Government as a payment card, not a credit card, and is a secure and controlled method of purchasing and paying for low value goods or services where it is used alongside other purchasing tools and processes.

If you require further information related to this dataset, please make a FOI request　using our online form.
